Option 4: If you know the Query ID of the INSERT (Best method)
Snowflake lets you find the exact INSERT query.
SELECT *
FROM TABLE(INFORMATION_SCHEMA.QUERY_HISTORY())
WHERE QUERY_TEXT ILIKE '%INSERT INTO SMS_OPT_IN%'
ORDER BY START_TIME DESC;
Get the Query ID.
Then see what rows were inserted:
SELECT *
FROM ASQN_PRD_ORCHESTRATION_DB.DBO.SMS_OPT_IN
BEFORE(STATEMENT => '<insert_query_id>');
Or compare before vs after and delete only those rows.
